Fig. 10
 shows the results, confirming the great stability of the prepared S, N-CQDs/ZnCo2O4 nanocomposite has in the 6 reaction cycles, so that only 23 percent of the photoactivity was lost after the total of 720 min of photocatalytic reaction. The attenuation of the photocatalytic activity could be clearly related to the detachment of S, N-CQDs from the surface of the ZnC2O4 nanoparticles. The EDX spectrum of the collected photocatalyst after each of the 6 cyclic reactions (Fig. 11
) revealed that the detachment of the S, N-CQDs caused slight reductions in the contents (wt%) of carbon, nitrogen and sulfur elements.
